,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"138DA6256D8F4287B6DD88FCFF8743BB","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/cuqyjbc6.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"90CC745900F64C1986CCDB709685F054","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/cuqyjbc6.png\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1101687,"guid":"74BA656052D011EB85BCBD5D2EC82AA4","previous_id":798601,"previous_guid":"2707AC00BED011E9B40F87B8D187FCE1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"726AF6CCE9184FD2BBAFD88A0687D87B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6040E70B39194217B318FCE5D499C32E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">1st selection:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>Using a sterile plastic pipette transfer the tissue from a single well into a 100 \u03bcm cell strainer, drain and then transfer on growth media containing the appropriate antibiotic. To facilitate spreading of the tissue, add 2 mL of sterile water to the petri dish - <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Figure 4.15-17<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\"><\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>Plate the tissue on solid KNOP plates supplemented with 100 \u03bcg\/mL cefotaxime and 10 \u03bcg\/mL Hygromycin and grow at 21\u00b0C  under 12 hours light and 12 hours dark, 35 \u03bcmol m<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">\u22122<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:super;\">s<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">\u22121<\/span><span><\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1101688,"guid":"522442D052D211EB85BCBD5D2EC82AA4","previous_id":1101687,"previous_guid":"74BA656052D011EB85BCBD5D2EC82AA4","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8E96F9FC71EC4CFB8C80BD7AC6AD0438","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C81AA010A5B942F1BEC17E9C2513263D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">2nd selection:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>After 3 weeks transfer the tissue to fresh growth media containing 100 \u03bcg\/mL cefotaxime and 10 \u03bcg\/mL Hygromycin. To facilitate spreading of tissue on the petri dish  add 2 mL of sterile water. Grow at 21\u00b0C  under 12 hours light and 12 hours dark, 35 \u03bcmol m<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">\u22122<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:super;\">s<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">\u22121<\/span><span>  - <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Figure 4.18<\/span><span><\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>After 6-8 weeks successful transformants are visible on the petri dish (successful transformants can be identified using a microscope after 4 weeks selection based on rhizoid production) - <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Figure 4.19 and Figure 5 & 6.<\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1101689,"guid":"CD9A3FA052D211EB85BCBD5D2EC82AA4","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F15F88F4A8FE4274BB26607C2C72A547","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F4277579F28348A99F3DD81A43EFFEE7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">IMPORTANT<\/span><span>: The light intensity used to cultivate <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">A. agrestis <\/span><span>tissue is a very critical factor for successful transformation. Tissue should be grown under low light intensity (3-5 \u03bcmol m<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">\u22122<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:super;\">s<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">\u22121<\/span><span>) and should have a morphology similar to the tissue in <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Figure 1<\/span><span> bottom left image.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":[{"id":12,"title":"Critical step","icon":"CriticalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1101690,"guid":"D7A581D052D211EB85BCBD5D2EC82AA4","previous_id":1101686,"previous_guid":"A3457C4052CF11EB85BCBD5D2EC82AA4","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AB62B801D84C4BBFA6